"title": "6040: sinners",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "6040: sinners",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>All who have sinned. The term tends to be used in particular of those regarded as outside God's covenant of grace, whose sins are therefore not forgiven.</p>\n<h2>The universality of sinful behaviour</h2>\n<h3>Only Jesus Christ is sinless</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:22\">1PE 2:22</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa53:9\">ISA 53:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor5:21\">2CO 5:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb4:15\">HEB 4:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb7:26\">HEB 7:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John3:5\">1JN 3:5</a></p>\n<h3>Everyone else has sinned</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal3:22\">GAL 3:22</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs8:46\">1KI 8:46</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom3:9-Rom3:19\">ROM 3:9–3:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom3:23\">ROM 3:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom5:12\">ROM 5:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom5:19\">ROM 5:19</a></p>\n<h2>God's mercy towards sinners</h2>\n<h3>God graciously extends mercy to sinners within the covenant</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps25:8-Ps25:10\">PSA 25:8–25:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs8:30\">1KI 8:30</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps86:5\">PSA 86:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps130:8\">PSA 130:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan9:9\">DAN 9:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John1:9\">1JN 1:9</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ died for sinners</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom5:8\">ROM 5:8</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim1:15\">1TI 1:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:3\">ROM 8:3</a></p>\n<h2>Sinners as those whose behaviour excludes them from God's covenant</h2>\n<h3>Prostitutes, tax collectors, idolatrous Gentiles and the ungodly</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke15:1\">LUK 15:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut23:17-Deut23:18\">DEU 23:17–23:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam15:18\">1SA 15:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke3:12\">LUK 3:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke7:37-Luke7:38\">LUK 7:37–7:38</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal2:15\">GAL 2:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess4:5\">1TH 4:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet4:18\">1PE 4:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov11:31\">PRO 11:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet2:5-2Pet2:6\">2PE 2:5–2:6</a></p>\n<h3>Such sinners shunned by the Jews</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke7:39\">LUK 7:39</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps1:1\">PSA 1:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov1:10-Prov1:16\">PRO 1:10–1:16</a></p>\n<h2>The judgment of sinners</h2>\n<h3>Prayers seeking their judgment</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps104:35\">PSA 104:35</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps109:6-Ps109:20\">PSA 109:6–109:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps137:7-Ps137:9\">PSA 137:7–137:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps139:19\">PSA 139:19</a></p>\n<h3>They are cut off from God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa59:2\">ISA 59:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps66:18\">PSA 66:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov15:29\">PRO 15:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa1:15\">ISA 1:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John9:31\">JHN 9:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor6:9-1Cor6:10\">1CO 6:9–6:10</a></p>\n<h3>They receive their just reward</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov13:21-Prov13:22\">PRO 13:21–13:22</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps1:5\">PSA 1:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps34:16\">PSA 34:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps37:38\">PSA 37:38</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl2:26\">ECC 2:26</a></p>\n<h3>Prophecies of their judgment</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa1:28\">ISA 1:28</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa13:9\">ISA 13:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa33:14\">ISA 33:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer4:18\">JER 4:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos9:10\">AMO 9:10</a></p>\n<h3>Their final judgment</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet3:7\">2PE 3:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa66:24\">ISA 66:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Thess1:8-2Thess1:9\">2TH 1:8–1:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet2:9\">2PE 2:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jude1:15\">JUD 1:15</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ's attitude towards sinners</h2>\n<h3>Jesus Christ's association with sinners</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:9-Matt9:13\">MAT 9:9–9:13</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark2:14-Mark2:17\">MRK 2:14–2:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke5:27-Luke5:32\">LUK 5:27–5:32</a> <em>Jesus Christ's attitude and behaviour were radically different from that of his contemporaries.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke15:1-Luke15:10\">LUK 15:1–15:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke19:5-Luke19:10\">LUK 19:5–19:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom5:8\">ROM 5:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim1:15-1Tim1:16\">1TI 1:15–1:16</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ extended God's forgiveness to sinners and welcomed them into his kingdom</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt21:31-Matt21:32\">MAT 21:31–21:32</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:2-Matt9:7\">MAT 9:2–9:7</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark2:3-Mark2:12\">MRK 2:3–2:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke5:18-Luke5:25\">LUK 5:18–5:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke7:40-Luke7:50\">LUK 7:40–7:50</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke15:11-Luke15:32\">LUK 15:11–15:32</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke18:9-Luke18:14\">LUK 18:9–18:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke19:9\">LUK 19:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John8:3-John8:11\">JHN 8:3–8:11</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ's behaviour led to accusations that he himself was a sinner</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John9:16\">JHN 9:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John9:24\">JHN 9:24</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ's refusal to accept sinful behaviour</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John8:10-John8:11\">JHN 8:10–8:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt4:17\">MAT 4:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt18:8-Matt18:9\">MAT 18:8–18:9</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark9:43-Mark9:48\">MRK 9:43–9:48</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John5:14\">JHN 5:14</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ's use of the example of sinners to teach his disciples</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke6:32-Luke6:34\">LUK 6:32–6:34</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:46-Matt5:47\">MAT 5:46–5:47</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke16:1-Luke16:9\">LUK 16:1–16:9</a></p>\n<h2>Sinners in the church</h2>\n<h3>Those who fall into sin should be restored</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas5:19-Jas5:20\">JAS 5:19–5:20</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps51:13\">PSA 51:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt18:12-Matt18:15\">MAT 18:12–18:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal6:1\">GAL 6:1</a></p>\n<h3>Unrepentant sinners should be expelled</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt18:15-Matt18:17\">MAT 18:15–18:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor5:9-1Cor5:11\">1CO 5:9–5:11</a></p>",
